narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Reactors, Separation Principles, Membranes, Heat Transfer, Distillation, and about Colloids. Lots of practical work with reactors
Learned a lot about chemical engineer lab techniques and the techniques they use
I developed skills in lab techniques essential for chemical engineering, as well as scientific writing ability.
Practicing different concepts throughout the ChemE education in the lab

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths:
- fairly organized
- opportunities for help
- decently interesting labs
- cool equipment

Weaknesses:
- lab reports sometimes unclear
- lab procedures sometimes unclear
I thought the course was strong
This course was very interesting and well taught!
It is tough to recall everything from past Chem E classes when writing the lab reports. The lab reports are also long and tedious
I like the structure of the lab. It felt like it could be a junior year class, but most people ended up doing it their last semester.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Lab reports are long, so only if youre interested in the course
Yes, I would recommend, because it is very informative and you gain vital skills.
You probably have to if you are in ChemE. It is a nice lab class.
